      "message": "i see the problem: I don\u0027t think we should use QueryArtifacts in this case, because invocation-level artifacts of sub-invocations have little to do with test results in the current invocation. Consider a situation:\n- build B scheduled a task T to run some tests\n- T ran some tests, and then attached syslogs as invocation-level artifacts\n- B also ran some of its own tests, and also attached its own syslogs to the B\u0027s invocation\n\nnow when we display B\u0027s test results, we also display syslogs of B (correct), but also syslogs of other machines.",
